G5590.definition: breath, i.e. (by implication) spirit, abstractly or concretely (the animal sentient principle only; thus distinguished on the one hand from G4151 (πνεῦμα), which is the rational and immortal soul; and on the other from G2222 (ζωή), which is mere vitality, even of plants: these terms thus exactly correspond respectively to the Hebrew H05315, H07307 and H02416)
G5590.kjvUsage: heart (+ -ily), life, mind, soul, + us, + you

G5591.definition: sensitive, i.e. animate (in distinction on the one hand from G4152 (πνευματικός), which is the higher or renovated nature; and on the other from G5446 (φυσικός), which is the lower or bestial nature)

G5594.definition: to breathe (voluntarily but gently, thus differing on the one hand from G4154 (πνέω), which denotes properly a forcible respiration; and on the other from the base of G109 (ἀήρ), which refers properly to an inanimate breeze), i.e. (by implication, of reduction of temperature by evaporation) to chill (figuratively)

G5595.definition: to supply with bits, i.e. (generally) to nourish

G5596.definition: a crumb or morsel (as if rubbed off), i.e. a mouthful
G5596.derivation: diminutive from a derivative of the base of G5597 (ψώχω);

G5597.definition: to triturate, i.e. (by analogy) to rub out (kernels from husks with the fingers or hand)
G5597.derivation: prolongation from the same base as G5567 (ψάλλω);

G5598.definition: the last letter of the Greek alphabet, i.e. (figuratively) the finality

G5599.definition: as a sign of the vocative case, O; as a note of exclamation, oh

G5600.definition: (may, might, can, could, would, should, must, etc.; also with G1487 (εἰ) and its comparative, as well as with other particles) be
G5600.kjvUsage: + appear, are, (may, might, should) be, X have, is, + pass the flower of her age, should stand, were

G5602.definition: in this same spot, i.e. here or hither
G5602.derivation: from an adverb form of G3592 (ὅδε);

G5603.definition: a chant or "ode" (the general term for any words sung; while G5215 (ὕμνος) denotes especially a religious metrical composition, and G5568 (ψαλμός) still more specially, a Hebrew cantillation)

G5604.definition: a pang or throe, especially of childbirth

G5605.definition: to experience the pains of parturition (literally or figuratively)

G5606.definition: the shoulder (as that on which burdens are borne)
G5606.derivation: perhaps from the alternate of G5342 (φέρω);

G5608.definition: to purchase (synonymous with the earlier G4092 (πίμπρημι))
G5608.derivation: middle voice from an apparently primary (a sum or price);

G5610.kjvUsage: day, hour, instant, season, X short, (even-)tide, (high) time

G5611.definition: belonging to the right hour or season (timely), i.e. (by implication) flourishing (beauteous (figuratively))

G5612.derivation: middle voice of an apparently primary verb;

G5613.definition: which how, i.e. in that manner (very variously used, as follows)
G5613.derivation: probably adverb of comparative from G3739 (ὅς);
G5613.kjvUsage: about, after (that), (according) as (it had been, it were), as soon (as), even as (like), for, how (greatly), like (as, unto), since, so (that), that, to wit, unto, when(-soever), while, X with all speed

G5614.definition: oh save!; hosanna (i.e. hoshia-na), an exclamation of adoration

G5615.definition: as thus, i.e. in the same way
G5615.derivation: from G5613 (ὡς) and an adverb from G846 (αὐτός);
G5615.kjvUsage: even so, likewise, after the same (in like) manner

G5616.kjvUsage: about, as (it had been, it were), like (as)

G5619.definition: just as if, i.e. as it were

G5620.definition: so too, i.e. thus therefore (in various relations of consecution, as follow)
G5620.kjvUsage: (insomuch) as, so that (then), (insomuch) that, therefore, to, wherefore

G5621.definition: an earlet, i.e. one of the ears, or perhaps the lobe of the ear

G5622.derivation: from a derivative of the base of G5624 (ὠφέλιμος);

G5623.definition: to be useful, i.e. to benefit
